Articles.Content:
is it just me or does someone alse having a problem with fuel configs where you make it so that a certin part has LFO in and then when you leave it in space and come bask to it it only has liquid fuel but no oxedizer or none at all?

thx for the help

On 8/2/2016 at 1:38 PM, prelog15 said:

is it just me or does someone alse having a problem with fuel configs where you make it so that a certin part has LFO in and then when you leave it in space and come bask to it it only has liquid fuel but no oxedizer or none at all?

thx for the help

I won't be able to help you, but I can tell you how to get the help you need and want -- provide logs, and make sure Firespitter and Interstellar Fuel Switch (among other plugins) are up to date. Stali or one of the other modders will take a look at your log file end either tell you how to fix it (if for some reason the problem is on your end) or they'll fix it in the next release of the mod (if the problem is a bug in the mod that they might have missed).

On 7/30/2016 at 0:13 AM, stali79 said:

At this stage the mod is currently not in achive development until November when @K.Yeon returns.  That being said i am making a note of suggestions to forward to him once he returns. One thing though that the custodial team and I would like to do is merge that cockpit with its adapter part but it is low on the list of priorities. The tail was removed from the old J parts as it had no ramp, K.Yen scrapped that series before completing it.

 

Another thing we are considering is adding adapters to make more of the parts interchangeable with each other but again this is low on the priority list.

 

Thank you for your suggestions and they have been noted.

appreciate the reply. This is tied for my top 3 mods along with suicidal insanity's mk2/3 and KSPI-E; the better it gets, the better all of modded KSP gets in my opinion.

but seriously, keep up the good work :3

I've had this problem before. it has to do with conflicting patches. Try COMPLETELY removing Interstellar Fuels, then downloading and installing the latest version. also, make sure you don't have any old "all fuels to all tanks" IF patches, they can mess with mod specific IF patches like the one in OPT.

Hey I'm having a problem with this most favorite mod of mine. I just caved and updated KSP 1.1.3 (I didn't want to because mod compatibility is kaput). When I checked out OPT, the cockpits all work. But the fuel tanks, crew tanks, and science tanks for the J,K,L, and a couple others did not work. Not only for animations when applicable, but also to select fuel types and what not. They were just a bunch of static place holder parts. Has anyone had this problem, any fixes? EDIT: Did some reading on these pages and Firespitter could be a problem but its up to date as far as I can tell. I downloaded everything straight off SpaceDock just now to make sure I had the latest OPT.

Edited August 5, 2016 by Victorsaurus
wut??

As has been repeated MANY times, if you cannot fuel your tanks then it means your firespitter is NOT up to date.

 

Edit: the firespitter bundled with OPT on spacedock is not for 1.1.3 but for 1.1.1. When I released 1.8.1.2, ksp 1.1.3 did not exist yet.

Edited August 5, 2016 by stali79

This mod is basically for parts, it does use Firespitter for the fuel switching options and while that is included with this mod for completeness, it is always best to go directly to the source for the latest files, especially if you're having problems.

Can anyone help me figure out why the demo version refuses to work on my install? I have reinstalled the mod four times and redownloaded KSP. Yet it still refuses to work. I have the latest version of IFS installed, as well as module manager, but still NONE and I mean NONE of the parts refused to show up in my otherwise stock install.  I finally gave up the idea of using OPT in my 1.1.3 install for now. So I decided to try downloading B9 Aerospace and for some arcane reason, that persuaded the large landing gear (which looks awesome, by the way) to show up.  Does anybody know what is wrong with my install? I know I for sure installed the mod correctly. That's the first thing I checked. I think I've checked that something like ten times now. I'm beginning to think the Kraken has taken up a permanent living space in my computer or something.

I'm running 1.1.3, by the way.

Evident in your post are a couple of atrocious misunderstandings, FYI. 

1. The fact that the issue with FireSpitter has been repeated many times means it is not a needle in a haystack; it is common. It's likely that you would have found an answer to your question without much effort, because it is common, and because you don't have to look through 78 pages to find it: only the last couple of pages in order to see if someone else has asked the same thing. The issue is that it is clear from your question that you didn't take the initiative in that respect.

2. The forum name of the person currently updating this mod is stali79. The name of the person who originally made this mod and posted the thread is K.Yeon. That means the first post of the thread does not belong to stali79. As a result, so far as I know, he cannot simply update the post on the first page.

3. It seems like you have a fundamental misconception of what to expect when updating KSP, because it appears you think KJR, MechJeb, etc. are a part of it - they are not. Squad is responsible for KSP, but they have no control over third-party modifications to the game. As third-party mods, KJR, MechJeb, FireSpitter and such must be adapted to the base game when it changes, not the other way around. You will forever be disappointed if you expect KSP and third-party mods (or any program and third-party mods) to continue functioning together when a bunch of code in the game is changed. When they do keep working well together, it's an unexpectedly happy occurrence. In light of all of that, what you say bout 1.1.3 not being ready for release doesn't make sense - except if you had mentioned wheels, of course, or minor bugs that persist in 1.1.3. Still, in the case of wheels, at least, Squad did the best with what was actually possible given their tools.

I hope that helps you understand what you are asking for and why you would receive a peevish response on the ol' internet.
